  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddPartController
    The AddPartController class is the controller class for the Add Part screen.
    AddProductController
    The AddProductController class is the controller class for the Add Product screen.
    InHouse
    The InHouse class is a subclass of the Part superclass allowing definition of the machine ID.
    Inventory
    The Inventory class provides data definition and manipulation methods to be used by the application.
    Inventory_GUIController
    Inventory_GUIController is the controller class for the main inventory screen.
    InventoryApp
    Class InventoryApp launches the Inventory Application.
    ModPartController
    ModPartController is the controller class for the Modify Part screen.
    ModProductController
    The ModProductController class is the controller class for the Modify Product screen.
    Outsourced
    The Outsourced class is a subclass of the Part superclass allowing definition of the company name.
    Part  
    Product
    The Product class contains the product constructor, setters, getters, and methods for part association and disassociation.
